  123.   method mark_tailcall : unit
  124.   (* informs the code emitter that the current function may end with
  125.      a tail-call; by default, does nothing *)

  127.   method mark_c_tailcall : unit
  128.   (* informs the code emitter that the current function may call
  129.      a C function that never returns; by default, sets
  130.      [contains_calls := true] in [-g] mode and does nothing otherwise.

  132.      It is unnecessary to save the stack pointer in this situation,
  133.      unless we need to produce exact stack backtraces, hence the default
  134.      definition.

  136.      Some architectures still need to ensure that the stack is properly
  137.      aligned when the C function is called, regardless of [-g].
  138.      This is achieved by overloading this method to set
  139.      [contains_calls := true]. *)
